# IP Geolocation Service — manual HTTP tests
# Run with: JetBrains HTTP Client or VS Code REST Client

### Look up a known public IP
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/geolocation/8.8.8.8
Accept: application/json

###

### Look up another public IP
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/geolocation/1.1.1.1
Accept: application/json

###

### Detect geolocation of the requesting client
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/geolocation/me
Accept: application/json

###

### Simulate a client behind a proxy using X-Forwarded-For
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/geolocation/me
Accept: application/json
X-Forwarded-For: 8.8.8.8

###

### Invalid IP format — expect HTTP 422
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/geolocation/not-an-ip
Accept: application/json

###

### Private IP — expect HTTP 422
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/v1/geolocation/192.168.1.1
Accept: application/json

###
